Attention 5th and 6th grade band/choir parents:
We wanted you to be aware that we will be focusing on choir the first semester and will not be starting band. The administrative team will be doing a complete inventory of all instruments to assess the quality and quantity of school owned instruments. If you do not want to do the rent to own instrument program you signed up for, please call the elementary school and ask for Mrs. Jones. If at any time you have questions about choir class, please call Mrs. Jones. Thank you!

Stanton County USD 452
September 4 at 9:12 PM ·

Beginning Wednesday, September 9th, USD #452 will be providing a free breakfast and a free lunch, Monday through Friday to any child ages 1-18. Any non school aged child who wishes to participate needs to sign up in advance. You may contact Sara Cox at sara.cox@usd452.org to sign up. Meals must be picked up at The junior/senior high school or the elementary school. Breakfast is served from 7:45-8:05 am, grab and go breakfast is served from 9:00-9:50 am and lunch is served from 11:00 am to 1:30 pm.

post_text:
Please remember the first day of school for Stanton County Schools is tomorrow August 13th. All students, staff, and visitors must wear a mask while indoors. If you don’t have one, the district will provide one. Additionally, the drinking fountains have been turned off. The bottle fill stations will be available and students are encouraged to bring a water bottle. If you don’t have one the district will provide one.

Remote learners need to pick up materials on Friday.

PreK does NOT start until Monday, August 17. The AM session is from 8:00 am to 11:30 am and the PM session is from 12:00 pm to 3:30 pm.

Have a great first day of school and welcome back!

post_text: Wearing a mask isn’t always easy, but it is worth it if it means getting to teach children face to face again. Please help set a positive tone for this new change. Here are a few things that might help: have your kid practice wearing a mask, pick a mask that fits their face, allow them to help pick the design, and explain the purpose for wearing the mask. (The district will provide a cloth mask with adjustable straps if you prefer.) We can do this Trojans!!!

SCES Students/Parents:
Work hard and enjoy your last week of school! Assignments will be accepted until May 17th. Chromebook check in will be on May 18th from 7:30 am - 5:30 pm at the front of the elementary school. Please have your Chromebook, charger, mouse, and any library or classroom textbooks with you. Individual and spring pictures will be handed out that day. Grade cards will be mailed the following week.

Stanton County Health Department
April 15 at 7:33 PM ·

There are currently 2 CONFIRMED Covid cases in Stanton County, all close contacts have been notified.

We will be notifying the public on each new positive COVID case through Civic Ready

If you have not yet signed up for Civic Ready, please message us through this source:
1. Your first and last name
2. Telephone number
3. Physical address
4. Email address
5. Let us know how you would like to be contacted (call, text, email, or all)
and we will gladly add you to Civic Ready to receive all important notifications. If you prefer to be contacted in Spanish, please let us know.

Thank you for continuing to stay home and practicing good hygiene habits!

USD # 452 está siguiendo la guía de los funcionarios de salud del condado con respecto a sus empleados. En este momento, ningún empleado de la escuela está en su lista de contactos cercanos, por lo que necesita estar en cuarentena. ¡La administración de la escuela se mantiene en contacto cercano con los funcionarios de salud del condado y cuando ellos indiquen que necesitamos poner en cuarentena a un empleado, lo haremos! Estamos tomando todas las precauciones de seguridad para permitir que nuestro personal continúe brindando funciones críticas a nuestra escuela y Stanton Co

¡ATENCIÓN A TODAS LAS FAMILIAS DE SCES!

Mañana, 26 de marzo, será nuestra recogida en la esquina para el libro de computadora, los libros de texto, los recursos y los artículos personales de su hijo. Deténgase al frente de la escuela primaria y espere en su automóvil hasta que nadie esté en la mesa. Se le entregará una caja con los artículos de su hijo. Por favor, preste mucha atención al siguiente horario. ¡Nos vemos mañana!

9:00 am - 10:00 am: apellidos de la A a la E

10:00 am - 11:00 am: apellidos de F a J

11:00 am - 12:00 pm: apellidos de K a O

1:00 pm - 2:00 pm: apellidos de P a T

2:00 pm - 3:00 pm: apellidos de la U a la Z

Si no puede recoger sus artículos debido a una cuarentena u otros motivos, llame al 620-492-6216 y los enviaremos a su porche.

Tomorrow, March 26th will be our curbside pick-up for your child’s chromebook, textbooks, resources, and personal items. 10:00 am - 11:00 am: Last names from F to J

11:00 am - 12:00 pm: Last names from K to O

Gracias a Pioneer Communications por instalar un punto de acceso wifi en el estacionamiento de High School. Los estudiantes y la comunidad pueden usarlo siempre que practique un distanciamiento social seguro.

Pedimos que la comunidad respete el uso de los estudiantes primero, mientras que Pioneer trabaja para que Internet llegue a sus hogares, esta puede ser la única forma en que pueden hacer su tarea durante el cierre de la escuela Covid-19 (Coronavirus).

Recuerde que esta sigue siendo una conexión filtrada, así que úsela SOLAMENTE para uso apropiado para la escuela.

Nuevamente, gracias a Pioneer Communications por proporcionar este servicio comunitario en este momento de necesidad.

post_text:
Monday starts a new chapter in public education. There is a huge learning curve that students and teachers will be navigating together!! 🙏🏼💻📒🔬📲💡🖇📝🔑As we move closer to embarking on this thing called “eLearning,” I am asking my Facebook friends to refrain from publicly scrutinizing their children’s teachers/schools for the way they are teaching or the lessons they are assigning. They are about to navigate uncharted territory with little, to no, preparation time. They are figuring this out as they go. Please be patient with them. This is a national crisis. We love your kids, we love what we do, and we are doing our absolute best! ❤️
#BetterTogether

Please copy & paste if you are an educator.

Some schools & districts have already started. We will have some growing pains for the teacher, student & parents. In the end we are all trying to do what’s BEST for our students.

post_text: Kansas Governor has mandated all schools in Kansas be closed to normal activities until the end of May. This doesn’t mean there is no school. All students will be out of school next week. Faculty and staff of USD 452 will meet next week to develop a continual learning plan to be implemented for the remainder of the school year. Guidance in the development of the continual learning plan is being provided by KSDE. The plan can include online learning, paper packets sent home, small group learning at the school or any other strategy developed by the faculty and staff that is approved by KSDE as part of the continual learning plan. Look for information tonight or tomorrow from the superintendent’s office.

post_text:
Mr. Mirabal took a handful of 5th/6th graders to the league math competition today. The 5th graders won the overall competition!!! Individual results are below.
Landry Waldron: 10th in geometry and 9th in problem solving
Kynzi Fehringer: 6th in mental math, 5th in geometry, and 3rd in problem solving
Hannah Canny: 10th in problem solving and 7th in geometry
Isabella Muro: 9th in mental math and was the champion for geometry and problem solving
Karlee Nairn: 8th in problem solving
Other participants: Avery Scott, Aurora Walker, and Karla Bautista
Congratulations to all of these students for making the team and for making us all proud!

post_text:
PARA-PROFESSIONAL POSITION

USD #452, Stanton County Schools has openings for Para-Professional.

Candidates must have the ability to communicate and work cooperatively with students, staff, and the ability to work without direct supervision.

Qualifications: Bilingual preferred, High School diploma or GED, sixty college hours, or pass the Para-Pro test. Benefits include KPERS retirement, participation in district health insurance and paid leave. Salary is commensurate with experience and qualifications. Applications available at the USD 452 District Office, or by calling 620-492-6226. Position is open until filled.
